"The five, some with wigs and others with naturally curly hair, were herded into the jail Tuesday night by deputy sheriffs who said they learned some bubble and strip tease dances were being staged at the night club. They all pleaded not guilty to charges of outraging public decency when arraigned before Charles W. Conner, common pleas judge. W. J. Stander, manager of the club also pleaded not guilty to the charge and was placed in jail in lieu of $1,000 bond. The other five charged are Frances Lee, 206 South Robinson avenue, Joe LaMar, Cincinnati, Ohio; Gene Marlee, Cincinnati; Jackie Dayton, Detroit, Mich., and Paul Gilvre, Terre Haute, Ind."
